HEADWORD: Benzoyl
<hw>Ben"zoyl</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Benzoic</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ wood. See <er>-yl</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
compound radical, <chform>C6H5.CO-</chform>; the base of benzoic acid,
of the oil of bitter almonds, and of an extensive series of
compounds.</def> <altsp>[Formerly written also
<asp>benzule</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

